## Your job

Perform the FULL change-and-self-review cycle for this issue in ONE session. The orchestrator handles git commit, push, and PR creation AFTER you finish.

## Workflow (MANDATORY - follow in order)

### Step 1: Make code changes
Address the issue. {% if require_new_test %}You MUST add at least one new test or modify an existing test as part of your change.{% endif %}

### Step 2: Verify
Run `{{ verify_cmd }}`. Iterate on the code until it exits 0.

### Step 3: Self-review
{% if reviewer_skill_installed %}Invoke the reviewer subagent on your work:

> @reviewer please review the changes I just made on the current branch (compared to `{{ base }}`). Report ALL findings at every severity (critical, high, medium, low, info).

The reviewer is a READ-ONLY subagent - it will not modify your code. It returns a structured list of findings.{% else %}Run opencode's built-in code review on your work:

> /review the changes I just made on the current branch (compared to `{{ base }}`). Report ALL findings at every severity (critical, high, medium, low, info).

The review is READ-ONLY - it will not modify your code. It returns a structured list of findings.{% endif %}

### Step 4: Address every finding
For each finding the reviewer returned - regardless of severity (critical, high, medium, low, info - fix them all):
  - Make the requested change
  - After all findings addressed, re-run `{{ verify_cmd }}` to confirm nothing broke

If you genuinely disagree with a finding, you may push back - document WHY in the PR body.

### Step 5: Re-review loop
Repeat Steps 3–4 up to {{ budget_attempts }} times, until the reviewer reports no remaining findings or the budget is exhausted.

### Step 6: Write the PR description
Write a markdown PR description to `.nocturne-pr-body.md` in the worktree root.

Required format:

```
# <One-line summary, imperative form, ≤ 72 chars>

<Multi-paragraph body: what changed, why, how tests cover it, any tradeoffs.>

Closes #{{ issue_number }}
```

The first `# ` line becomes the PR title AND the commit message subject. Everything below becomes the PR body on GitHub.

### Step 7: Stop
Do NOT commit. Do NOT push. Do NOT run `git commit`, `git push`, `git branch`, `git checkout`, `git merge`, `git rebase`, or `gh pr` of any kind. The orchestrator handles all git operations using your `.nocturne-pr-body.md`.

You are on branch `{{ branch }}`; do not switch branches or modify `main`.

